Vheadline
p2
VSoaked in devotion and melody
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe invocatory piece, a virutham, and &#8216;Gam Ganapathaye namo namo&#8217; on Lord Ganesa, composed by Muthayya Bhagavathar  Hamsadhwani, set to Adi tala (Thisra gathi), was embellished with lively chittaswara.She was well supported by Anoop Bhaskaran on the violin and Ganesh Varma on the mridangam. Dikshitar&#8217;s &#8216;Ardhanareeswaram&#8217;  in  Kumudakriya, set to Roopaka tala, was aesthetically articulated and soaked in devotion.&#8216;Ma Mayoorameethleri va,&#8217; composed by Chidambara Bharathi, was adorned with impressive chittaswara and brilliant swara kalpana.  &#8216;Divakara thanujam Sanaischaram,&#8217; one of the Navagraha kritis of Dikshitar, a hymn on Lord Saneeswara, deity of the temple venue, in Yadukulakamboji, was sung with utmost piety.An erudite rendition of Lathangi, the 63rd Melakartharaga, brought to fore the intricacies and nuances of the raga, harmonising both Lakshya and Lakshana. &#8216;Venkata ramana&#8217; composed by Papanasam Sivan, set to Roopaka tala, was decorated with  niraval and  kalpanaswara at the sequence &#8216;Alarmel mangai manala&#8217;.Presentation of  Swati Tirunal&#8217;s majestic composition &#8216;Jananee mamava,&#8217; set to Misrachappu, conveyed the elegance of the composition.  Brilliant swarakalpana in ragamalika, comprising ragas Amrutha varshini, Sreeranjini, Saraswathi, Bahudari and Kalyani, was proof of her expertise as a singer.Some of the other pieces that were sung were a Tharangam by Narayana Theerthar, &#8216;Kalyana Gopalam&#8217; in Sindhubhairavi, &#8216;Chinnachinna padam vaithu&#8217; in  raga Kappi  and &#8216;Hanumanai anudinam&#8217; a ragamalika.The vocalist then showcased her rhythmic skill in the thillana composed by Lalitha Sivakumar in Valachi. The concert was wound up with a bhajan &#8216;Thiruppathi malai meethu irukkindra Perumane&#8217; in  Yamunakalyani and &#8216;Sree Ramachandranukku jayamangalam&#8217; in Madhyamavathi.Veteran Carnatic vocalist Janaki Venugopal was honoured and awarded  the title &#8216;Nadachandrika&#8217; by Swati Sangeetha Sabha, Palakkad. The concert was conducted in connection with the concert.
